---
import MainLayout from "../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import SectionHeader from "@/components/SectionHeader.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Uses"
  metaDesc="This page details pretty much all I use as a developer."
>
  <main
    id="main-content"
    tabindex="-1"
    class="max-w-[65ch] lg:max-w-[70ch] mx-auto px-6 py-12"
  >
    <article class="space-y-12">
      <header class="space-y-8">
        <SectionHeader title="Uses" />
      </header>

      <div class="space-y-8 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          This page details pretty much all I use as a developer. If you decide
          to make your own, consider adding it to <a
            href="https://twitter.com/wesbos"
            class="text-pink-600 font-semibold hover:underline focus:underline focus:outline-none"
            >Wes Bos</a
          >' <a
            href="https://uses.tech"
            class="text-pink-600 font-semibold hover:underline focus:underline focus:outline-none"
            >uses.tech</a
          >. I use a Mac, so most tools are macOS specific, but there are some
          OS-agnostic ones in the list. You might also be interested in <a
            href="http://localhost:4321/blog/from-fresh-mac-to-productive-in-30-minutes-21db"
            class="text-pink-600 font-semibold hover:underline focus:underline focus:outline-none"
            >My Mac Setup</a
          > post, although it is a little outdated.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          Note: This page contains affiliate links. I may earn a commission for
          purchases made through these links at no additional cost to you.
        </p>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900" id="heading-editor">
            Editor<a
              href="#heading-editor"
              class="heading-anchor"
              aria-label="Link to this section">#</a
            >
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>
              <a
                href="https://code.visualstudio.com"
                class="text-pink-600 font-semibold hover:underline focus:underline focus:outline-none"
                >VS Code</a
              > with GitHub Copilot and <a
                href="https://www.cursor.com"
                class="text-pink-600 font-semibold hover:underline focus:underline focus:outline-none"
                >Cursor</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              Themes: <a
                href="https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=astro-build.houston"
                class="text-pink-600 font-semibold hover:underline focus:underline focus:outline-none"
                >Houston</a
              > and the Default Light Modern theme.
            </li>
            <li>
              Font: <a
                href="https://philpl.gumroad.com/l/dank-mono"
                class="text-pink-600 font-semibold hover:underline focus:underline focus:outline-none"
                >Dank Mono</a
              > - A font I paid for, but I love it.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h3
            class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900"
            id="heading-chromeedgefirefox-browser-extensions"
          >
            Chrome/Edge/Firefox Browser Extensions<a
              href="#heading-chromeedgefirefox-browser-extensions"
              class="heading-anchor"
              aria-label="Link to this section">#</a
            >
          </h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>
              <a
                href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/refined-github/hlepfoohegkhhmjieoechaddaejaokhf"
                >Refined GitHub</a
              > - GitHub on steroids
            </li><li>
              <a
                href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/visbug/cdockenadnadldjbbgcallicgledbeoc?hl=en"
                >VisBug</a
              > - An awesome tool for frontend (this oneâ€™s new for me) (only for Chromium
              based browsers)
            </li><li>
              <a
                href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/react-developer-tools/fmkadmapgofadopljbjfkapdkoienihi?hl=en"
                >React DevTools</a
              > - Because React
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://preactjs.github.io/preact-devtools/"
                >Preact DevTools</a
              > - Because Preact
            </li><li>
              <a
                href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/axe-web-accessibility-tes/lhdoppojpmngadmnindnejefpokejbdd"
                >Axe</a
              > - For web accessibility testing
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://wave.webaim.org/extension/">WAVE</a> - For web accessibility
              testing
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://www.eff.org/https-everywhere">HTTPS Everywhere</a
              >
            </li><li><a href="https://ublock.org/">uBlock</a></li><li>
              <a href="https://languagetool.org">LanguageTool</a> - A grammar and
              spell checking tool
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://getpocket.com/">Pocket</a> - For bookmarking stuff
              to read
            </li><li>
              <a
                href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/jsonview/chklaanhfefbnpoihckbnefhakgolnmc"
                >JSONView</a
              > - A prettified view of JSON payloads
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            id="heading-desktop-apps"
            class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900"
          >
            Desktop Apps<a
              href="#heading-desktop-apps"
              class="heading-anchor"
              aria-label="Link to this section">#</a
            >
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>
              <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/edge">Microsoft Edge</a> -
              My main browser for my day to day work and personal stuff.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://www.macbartender.com">Bartender</a> - For managing
              your menu bar. I used to use <a
                href="https://matthewpalmer.net/vanilla/">Vanilla</a
              >, but with the notch in newer MacBook Pros, Bartender made the
              menubar more usable when dealing with lots of menubar icons.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://matthewpalmer.net/rocket/">Rocket</a> - Emojis, emojis
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://raycast.com">Raycast</a> - Workflows, snippets, macOS
              spotlight on steroids. I previously used <a
                href="https://www.alfredapp.com/">Alfred</a
              >, another amazing Spotlight alternative.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://justgetflux.com/">f.lux</a> - Be kind to your eyeballs
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://git-fork.com/">Fork</a> - A great git GUI
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop"
                >Docker Desktop</a
              > - Because Docker
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://xscope.app">xScope</a> - Awesome toolset for frontend
              development. Rulers, guides etc.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://sindresorhus.com/dato">Dato</a> - A better date app
              for macOS. It's great for having multiple time zones in the address
              bar. I have my local time as well as UTC. I also use it for upcoming
              meetings and events. Previously I was using <a
                href="https://trymeeter.com">Meeter</a
              > which is great for this, but it's one less app I need now.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://ghostty.org">Ghostty</a> - A a fast, feature-rich,
              and cross-platform terminal emulator that uses platform-native UI and
              GPU acceleration.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://starship.rs/">Starship</a> - A cross shell prompt
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://www.spotify.com/us/download/">Spotify</a> - Because
              music.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://obsproject.com/download">OBS</a> - For streaming on
              Twitch
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://cleanshot.com/">Cleanshot X</a> - For better screenshots
              and screen recordings
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://blog.cloudflare.com/1111-warp-better-vpn/"
                >Cloudflare Warp</a
              > - Faster Internet and some VPN goodness
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://krisp.ai/">Krisp</a> - Filter out unwanted noise on
              calls and streams
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://gpgtools.org/">GPG Suite</a> - For all things GPG
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://www.figma.com/">Figma</a> - Design collaboratively
              on the web
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://rogueamoeba.com/loopback/">Loopback</a> - Great for
              virtual audio sources
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://macpaw.com/cleanmymac">CleanMyMac X</a> - A suite of
              utilities for keeping your Mac in tip top shape.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://reincubate.com/camo/">Camo</a> - Use your mobile devices
              as cameras for your OS.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://polypane.app/">Polypane</a> - A browser for helping
              develop responsive, more accessible and more performant websites.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 id="heading-clis" class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">
            CLIs<a
              href="#heading-clis"
              class="heading-anchor"
              aria-label="Link to this section">#</a
            >
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>
              <a href="https://brew.sh">Homebrew</a> - The Missing Package Manager
              for macOS (or Linux)
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://github.com/cli/cli">GitHub CLI</a> - GitHub on the
              command line. Great for creating PRs, etc.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm">nvm</a> - Node version manager
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://github.com/cloudflare/cloudflared">cloudflared</a
              > - Exposes local servers to the public internet over secure tunnels
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            id="heading-office-setup"
            class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900"
          >
            Office Setup<a
              href="#heading-office-setup"
              class="heading-anchor"
              aria-label="Link to this section">#</a
            >
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>
              2 x <a href="https://benqurl.biz/4kZ3mRx"
                >BenQ RD280U 28" 4K monitor</a
              >. One is on a stand and the other is on a swivel arm.
            </li><li>
              <a
                href="https://motiongrey.com/products/copy-of-motion-series-standing-desk-with-table-top?variant=39702825730141"
                >MotionGrey Adjustable Dual Motors Electric Sit to Stand
                Computer Office Standing Desk</a
              > - I snagged it at a great price. It appears to go on sale often.
            </li><li>
              Herman Miller Aeron office chair. These are pricey, so look out
              for one on online classifieds. I snagged one with many new parts
              for just under a third of the price.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3WzPZf4"
                >Rollerblade style caster wheels</a
              > (for office chair). Thanks for the suggestion <a
                href="https://www.ergosesh.com/">ErgoSesh</a
              >!
            </li><li>MacBook Pro 14" (2022)</li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3yqPvA4">Logitech MX Master 3 mouse</a>
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3SzSNba"
                >Logitech ERGO K860 wireless split keyboard</a
              >
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/4ftsjBT">Sony WH-1000XM3</a> headphones - I
              snagged them during Boxing Day week.
            </li><li>
              <a
                href="https://www.shure.com/en-US/products/microphones/mv7?variant=MV7%252B-K"
                >Shure MV7+ Microphone</a
              > - I use this for all my live streams and recordings. It's a great
              mic and I love the built in USB-C port. You can also use it with XLR
              if you want to go that route, but I don't atm. I opted for white to
              contrast with my black boom arm.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3WNsYqx"
                >RODE PSA1 Swivel Mount Studio Microphone Boom Arm</a
              >
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3yqdpvt"
                >Rain Design mStand360 Laptop Stand with Swivel Base</a
              >
            </li><li>iPhone 14 camera for streaming and recording video</li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3Ac5XVt"
                >Lamicall Gooseneck Phone Holder Bed</a
              > - I use this to hold my iPhone when I use it for a camera while live
              streaming or recording video.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/4dacHSa"
                >Anker USB C Hub, 5-In-1 USB C Adapter</a
              >
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3WQvQCQ"
                >Powered USB 3.0 Hub, WENTER 11-Port USB Data Hub</a
              >
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3WOt1Ck"
                >Logitech Litra Glow Premium LED Streaming Light with TrueSoft</a
              > - Lighting for live streaming and recording video. I have two of these
              and they're awesome.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3yguEj0"
                >Seagate Portable 5TB External Hard Drive HDD</a
              >
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3YyiUTw"
                >Topo Comfort Mat by Ergodriven</a
              > standing desk mat
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3YrjjXZ">LEVOIT Air Purifier Core 300</a>
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3YuyMq2">Elgato Streamd Deck XL</a> - Great
              for controlling scenes in OBS, dropping links and messages in chat,
              but I also use it for other apps like Spotify and Zoom.
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3ysolsC"
                >Quartet Glass Desktop Computer Pad, 18 inch x 6 inch</a
              >, a handy desk whiteboard. Thanks for the suggestion <a
                href="https://jhey.dev">Jhey</a
              >!
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 id="heading-travel-gear" class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">
            Travel Gear<a
              href="#heading-travel-gear"
              class="heading-anchor"
              aria-label="Link to this section">#</a
            >
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6">
            <li><a href="https://amzn.to/3LRrEfT">Roost Laptop Stand</a></li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3SB8Yom">Anker USB-C to HDMI Adapter</a>
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://www.amazon.ca/gp/product/B07YYTHMCG"
                >Jelly Comb Ultra Slim Folding Bluetooth Keyboard</a
              >
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3A5W4bE"
                >Anker Magnetic Battery, 10,000 mAh Foldable Wireless Portable
                Charger</a
              >
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://amzn.to/3yB2dMB">Apple Magic Trackpad (White)</a>
            </li><li>
              <a href="https://www.airalo.com/">Airalo</a> eSIMs for travel outside
              North America. A must have when travelling outside of your home country.
              Use the referral code
              <code>NICK1387</code> to get a discount off your first eSIM.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2 id="heading-other" class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900">
            Other<a
              href="#heading-other"
              class="heading-anchor"
              aria-label="Link to this section">#</a
            >
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>
              WISE for banking. I use it for my business. It's a great way to
              send money internationally without the crazy fees. Use this
              referral code to get started, <a
                href="https://wise.com/invite/dic/nicholast1738"
                >wise.com/invite/dic/nicholast1738</a
              >
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="space-y-4">
          <h2
            id="heading-health-and-training"
            class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900"
          >
            Health and Training<a
              href="#heading-health-and-training"
              class="heading-anchor"
              aria-label="Link to this section">#</a
            >
          </h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700 list-disc pl-6">
            <li>
              For my Canadian peeps. I've been ordering from <a
                href="https://farm2fork.refr.cc/default/u/taylor?s=pppw&t=tw"
                >Farm 2 Fork</a
              > and it's been really great and high quality. Here's a <a
                href="https://farm2fork.refr.cc/default/u/taylor?s=pppw&t=tw"
                >referral link</a
              > if you want to give it a go and get a discount!
            </li><li>
              <a
                href="https://www.nutratology.com/products/creatine-monohydrate"
                >Creatine Monohydrate from Nutratology</a
              >. Use the discount code <code>NICK_10</code> when purchasing.
            </li>
            <li>
              Kettlebells from <a href="https://matsuru.ca">Matsura</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>
</MainLayout>
